Hello FIRST Community,

I hope everyone is having a great day!! During the Offseason our team (FTC #18737) made a Marketplace for FIRST Teams to buy and sell parts.

Last season our team had a lot of issues getting parts quickly and at an affordable price. We also struggled with fundraising. We heard a lot of similar stories from other rookie teams throughout the season, and we believe that having a common marketplace where we can easily trade, sell and buy parts would be very beneficial for the FIRST community.

Here is the link to the site: https://firstmarketplace.org/

Do you have any available parts to list? We would like to get as many parts listed before the season starts so that rookie teams have a chance to get started and professional teams can expand their tools and capabilities.

Please note that the product is in beta and we are looking for any feedback or bugs you may encounter.

Thank you so much!
The Hexadecimals #18737

You used the correct FIRST standard logos for the other programs but used the wrong/old one for FRC.

Your header link FIRST Marketplace takes you to another home page with no way back to the Buy page. If your main site starts with the Buy page that title header link should direct to that.

Clicking the contact owner, then shows the please sign in button, clicking that button does nothing. I assume it should direct to the login page.

This site isn’t mobile friendly at all.
How did you architect it, fully custom html, css, js?

I would recommend you read carefully FIRST’s use of FIRST and LEGO trademarks document and think about how it applies to your site. Despite the fact you’re a FIRST team, using the logos may not be okay, and the site name overall may also be problematic due to the fact it may cause confusion (e.g. people might think this is a site run by FIRST itself). Most team-run projects avoid this by in some way using the team name instead of the FIRST name (Chief Delphi is one obvious example).
